WEBVTT

00:04.280 --> 00:06.560
_

00:06.620 --> 00:13.100
♪

00:13.360 --> 00:19.560
♪

00:23.140 --> 00:28.940
♪

00:29.010 --> 00:30.970
Sorry, miss,

00:31.010 --> 00:32.970
but you forgot your...

00:33.020 --> 00:34.710
My bag.

00:34.760 --> 00:36.760
It's not just a bag.

00:38.200 --> 00:39.600
It's a Ravenzo.

00:43.320 --> 00:44.760
- [MURMURING, APPLAUSE]
- MAN: Bravo.

00:45.850 --> 00:47.940
MAN: It's a beautiful bag.

00:47.980 --> 00:49.900
- WOMAN: Bravo.
- Buona sera.

00:49.940 --> 00:52.450
I am Sandro Ravenzo.

00:52.480 --> 00:55.950
And welcome to the launch
of our new Ravenzo bag.

00:55.990 --> 00:59.970
The Ravenzo name, it has
survived the Great Depression,

01:00.000 --> 01:01.500
two World Wars,

01:01.600 --> 01:05.740
2008, and one marriage to an American.

01:05.770 --> 01:08.980
[LAUGHTER, APPLAUSE]

01:11.200 --> 01:13.440
My mother, Francesca.

01:13.480 --> 01:14.960
[MURMURING, APPLAUSE]

01:15.010 --> 01:16.970
MAN: Wonderful.

01:17.010 --> 01:19.100
- Mm.
- Eh...

01:19.140 --> 01:21.260
Of course, I would be remiss

01:21.280 --> 01:23.410
if I did not thank my sister Giulia.

01:23.450 --> 01:25.360
- [APPLAUSE]
- WOMAN: Bravo.

01:25.420 --> 01:26.840
Bellissima.

01:28.200 --> 01:29.800
Thank you all for coming.

01:29.840 --> 01:33.860
And remember, you touch
it, you buy it. Yes?

01:33.880 --> 01:35.480
- [LAUGHTER, APPLAUSE]
- WOMAN: Good job.

01:40.100 --> 01:41.500
[QUIET CHATTER]

01:41.600 --> 01:43.210
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

01:43.250 --> 01:44.620
[CAMERA CLICKS]

01:49.140 --> 01:50.540
Bellissima.

01:50.570 --> 01:52.480
See you later.

01:52.520 --> 01:54.400
Get a hold of yourself.

01:54.440 --> 01:56.220
What are you talking about?

01:56.240 --> 01:58.820
Don't embarrass me tonight, please.

01:58.880 --> 02:01.080
And where have you been
spending your nights, Fiona?

02:05.420 --> 02:06.720
Give me the valet ticket.

02:09.740 --> 02:12.060
Sandro, go after her.

02:12.120 --> 02:16.200
Fiona. Fiona, wait.

02:22.640 --> 02:24.210
- Fiona.
- How can you stand there

02:24.250 --> 02:25.640
and praise this ugly family?

02:25.660 --> 02:27.210
What are you saying?

02:27.250 --> 02:28.360
Would it matter?

02:28.420 --> 02:30.840
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

02:34.080 --> 02:36.040
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

02:39.050 --> 02:41.000
[TIRES SCREECHING]

02:43.000 --> 02:49.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:51.300 --> 02:53.410
Hate to disappoint you,
Yates, but there doesn't seem

02:53.450 --> 02:57.200
to be any severed heads
in Cynthia's closet.

02:57.240 --> 02:58.440
Paintings.

02:58.470 --> 02:59.880
- Sculptures.
- Mm-hmm.

02:59.920 --> 03:01.580
No family photos.

03:01.600 --> 03:04.900
No evidence of any life
outside of this stuff.

03:04.940 --> 03:06.200
What does that tell you?

03:06.220 --> 03:08.630
That she's been burned by
nosy coworkers before.

03:08.640 --> 03:10.390
Come on, Zara. Don't you think Cynthia's

03:10.400 --> 03:12.540
- being a little evasive?
- No.

03:12.560 --> 03:15.600
Every time we hang out, she bails early.

03:15.720 --> 03:18.160
It's been eight months. I
feel like I barely know her.

03:18.210 --> 03:21.100
I'm not being nosy. I think
she's hiding something.

03:21.120 --> 03:22.159
Okay.

03:22.160 --> 03:25.140
Count me out of the "Who Is
Cynthia Walker?" sweepstakes.

03:25.160 --> 03:26.820
You're on your own.

03:26.870 --> 03:28.960
All right, you guys, let's eat.

03:29.000 --> 03:30.700
Mm.

03:34.260 --> 03:36.400
Wow.

03:36.440 --> 03:38.930
Escabèche snapper, braised lamb shank,

03:38.940 --> 03:40.630
topped with crispy fried shallots

03:40.640 --> 03:43.690
and parsnips beurre
blanc finished by Eric.

03:43.780 --> 03:45.240
Well, come on. I-I whisked.

03:45.260 --> 03:47.320
I didn't... I didn't finish anything.

03:47.450 --> 03:49.300
I can't do any of this.

03:49.320 --> 03:50.820
I'll take that as a compliment.

03:50.860 --> 03:52.460
Well, where did you learn to cook?

03:52.480 --> 03:54.420
Oh, I just pick things
up here and there.

03:54.440 --> 03:55.780
Must have been a big change,

03:55.800 --> 03:58.100
- moving back to Montreal.
- How so?

03:58.120 --> 04:01.100
You know, having all your family
and friends so close again.

04:01.290 --> 04:04.250
Oh, well, actually, my
parents were immigrants,

04:04.290 --> 04:05.740
and they died when I was young,

04:05.750 --> 04:07.480
so it's just me.

04:07.540 --> 04:08.920
Just you.

04:10.080 --> 04:11.699
I'd like to make a toast.

04:11.700 --> 04:14.160
No. My house, my toast.

04:14.170 --> 04:15.400
Uh, but I was gonna toast...

04:15.420 --> 04:18.870
This is not a negotiation,
Beaumont. Zip it.

04:18.920 --> 04:21.490
[LAUGHS]: All right, glasses up.

04:21.529 --> 04:22.660
[SIGHS]

04:22.700 --> 04:24.840
So, to finally cooking

04:24.880 --> 04:26.460
for you lovely people.

04:26.470 --> 04:28.330
When you live alone as long as I have,

04:28.360 --> 04:31.179
you forget how nice this is.

04:31.180 --> 04:32.600
How nice what is?

04:32.660 --> 04:33.800
Family.

04:36.400 --> 04:37.420
To Cri/Res.

04:37.880 --> 04:40.350
To Cri/Res.

04:40.460 --> 04:41.760
To family.

04:41.780 --> 04:43.940
- Welcome.
- Thank you.

04:45.420 --> 04:47.800
- _
- [BIRDS CHIRPING]

04:51.720 --> 04:55.870
Fiona, I have left you 25 messages.

04:55.910 --> 04:59.960
Would you please, please...

05:00.000 --> 05:01.820
pick up the phone?

05:02.460 --> 05:04.540
Please.

05:04.700 --> 05:07.380
Ferma! Ferma la macchina!

05:12.580 --> 05:14.640
Fiona!

05:14.760 --> 05:16.840
Fiona!

05:22.720 --> 05:26.700
_

05:32.080 --> 05:37.260
♪

