05:58.120 --> 06:00.290
MAN: It is in the best interest

06:00.320 --> 06:02.020
to not screw us around.

06:02.060 --> 06:03.600
We won't be lied to.

06:03.650 --> 06:04.820
Okay, no one's screwing you around.

06:04.840 --> 06:06.440
My name is Eric Beaumont.

06:06.460 --> 06:09.040
I was hired by the Ravenzos
to negotiate on their behalf.

06:09.060 --> 06:11.730
Now, before we begin, I need proof

06:11.770 --> 06:13.560
that Fiona Ravenzo is still alive.

06:17.400 --> 06:18.640
SANDRO: Oh, dio mio.

06:18.660 --> 06:20.180
Give me back my wife.

06:20.240 --> 06:23.020
- Animale. I will kill you.
- Oliver?

06:23.060 --> 06:24.570
CYNTHIA: Mr. Ravenzo,

06:24.580 --> 06:25.620
expressing emotion

06:25.630 --> 06:27.140
gives the kidnappers leverage.

06:27.160 --> 06:28.270
We will get your wife back,

06:28.310 --> 06:29.920
but you need to stay calm.

06:31.980 --> 06:33.740
[CYNTHIA CLEARS THROAT]

06:33.780 --> 06:35.920
ERIC: Thank you. It helps knowing

06:35.960 --> 06:38.740
that Fiona's alive and relatively well.

06:38.770 --> 06:39.780
Enough talk.

06:39.800 --> 06:42.720
How much is the Ravenzo
woman worth to you?

06:42.740 --> 06:45.640
Well, we're prepared to offer
you a substantial sum.

06:45.660 --> 06:47.080
It should be here...

06:47.120 --> 06:48.720
[QUIETLY]: One million, three hours.

06:48.780 --> 06:50.310
... very soon.

06:50.350 --> 06:52.860
We have 250,000 euro to offer.

06:52.880 --> 06:55.160
The Ravenzo family is worth a fortune,

06:55.170 --> 06:56.830
and you're offering me scraps?

06:56.880 --> 06:57.890
No, sir.

06:57.900 --> 06:59.840
Maybe I should just shoot her right now.

06:59.900 --> 07:02.690
Maybe I should just empty
my gun on her head.

07:02.730 --> 07:05.270
Emotionally, this guy's
all over the place, Eric.

07:05.280 --> 07:08.100
He has a beta personality.
He'll respond to an alpha.

07:08.140 --> 07:10.490
250,000 was my offer.

07:10.540 --> 07:13.540
You want to negotiate,
fine. Let's negotiate.

07:13.600 --> 07:16.800
But you make one more threat,
and you won't see a dime.

07:18.630 --> 07:20.980
We want a serious offer.

07:21.030 --> 07:22.719
It'll take some time, but I may be able

07:22.720 --> 07:24.500
to get that number up
to a half a million.

07:24.540 --> 07:27.180
We'll call back.

07:28.480 --> 07:31.780
[PHONE RINGING, VIBRATING]

07:31.800 --> 07:32.810
Zara, what have you got?

07:32.900 --> 07:36.139
ZARA: Skid marks indicate
Fiona was going very fast

07:36.140 --> 07:37.580
before she went off the road.

07:37.690 --> 07:39.860
It's a miracle anyone survived.

07:39.900 --> 07:41.740
Yeah, she had quite the cut to her head.

07:41.790 --> 07:43.050
Okay, I'll work fast.

07:43.090 --> 07:45.239
Zara, negotiating in Italy is illegal,

07:45.240 --> 07:47.419
so if the police show up, you...

07:47.420 --> 07:49.840
Just make an excuse and
get out of here. Got it.

07:49.880 --> 07:51.930
I'll call back when I have something.

08:03.550 --> 08:05.850
That car crash bother anyone else?

08:05.900 --> 08:08.220
Well, it's a risky way
to kidnap someone.

08:08.240 --> 08:09.460
Fiona could've been killed.

08:09.470 --> 08:11.950
And the kidnappers didn't come
at us with a fixed number.

08:11.990 --> 08:13.220
That's also new.

08:13.340 --> 08:15.340
So what does that tell us?

08:15.380 --> 08:16.940
They're making it up as they go.

08:17.000 --> 08:18.650
I don't think they
intended to kidnap her.

08:18.690 --> 08:20.520
Might have been a crime of opportunity.

08:20.560 --> 08:23.740
Driving along, find a crashed
car, rich woman inside.

08:23.780 --> 08:25.720
What about that call?
What did you pick up?

08:25.730 --> 08:27.140
Well, the fact that he
kept making threats

08:27.170 --> 08:29.570
and cutting you off implied
a deep sense of insecurity.

08:29.620 --> 08:30.959
Like fear of failure?

08:30.960 --> 08:32.360
Answering to someone important?

08:32.380 --> 08:34.480
That, or he's way out of his element.

08:34.539 --> 08:36.400
- [PHONE RINGING]
- Yeah.

08:38.630 --> 08:40.500
Hey, Zara. You're on speaker.

08:40.520 --> 08:42.669
ZARA: Hey, I found some deep tire marks.

08:42.720 --> 08:45.410
Not from Sandro's car, but on
the other side of a blind hill.

08:45.460 --> 08:48.160
Something big, maybe a dump truck?

08:48.200 --> 08:50.160
I'm guessing the kidnappers parked here

08:50.200 --> 08:52.100
knowing Fiona would come this way.

08:52.250 --> 08:55.240
Okay, so they were planning
something, but what?

08:55.250 --> 08:56.860
Looks like she swerved to avoid them

08:56.900 --> 08:58.160
and went off the road.

08:58.170 --> 09:00.579
- That's when they collected her.
- ZARA: Also...

09:00.580 --> 09:02.910
the ransom note was right where
Sandro said it would be,

09:02.950 --> 09:04.340
but he failed to mention it was written

09:04.360 --> 09:06.260
on the back of one of
his speeding tickets.

09:06.300 --> 09:07.940
Okay, that doesn't sound planned.

09:08.130 --> 09:11.280
And the seat belt on the
passenger side was cut, Eric.

09:11.300 --> 09:13.240
Tampered with before the crash.

09:13.300 --> 09:16.400
If she was sitting where she was
supposed to be, she'd be dead.

09:16.440 --> 09:18.970
She's only alive because
she was driving.

09:19.010 --> 09:21.200
Okay, so whoever took Fiona

09:21.220 --> 09:24.140
approached the car expecting to
find her in the passenger seat.

09:24.240 --> 09:28.170
Now, when they found her alive
and figured out who she was,

09:28.180 --> 09:30.110
they scribbled a note on
the only piece of paper

09:30.160 --> 09:31.440
they could find

09:31.470 --> 09:33.699
and took her for ransom instead.

09:33.700 --> 09:35.080
Instead of what?

09:35.140 --> 09:36.740
Instead of killing her.

09:38.340 --> 09:41.520
These men were hired as assassins.

09:47.900 --> 09:51.140
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

09:51.200 --> 09:52.830
Uh... mi scusi.

09:52.870 --> 09:54.020
Parla inglese?

09:55.700 --> 09:57.240
What are you doing here?

09:57.320 --> 09:59.540
I was driving by, and I saw the car.

09:59.600 --> 10:01.640
Wanted to make sure no
one was trapped inside.

10:01.680 --> 10:03.480
Was there?

10:03.560 --> 10:05.400
No.

10:06.220 --> 10:08.060
I hope you didn't touch anything.

10:08.110 --> 10:09.820
Don't worry, I know the drill.

10:09.880 --> 10:12.680
I used to be a cop like you. New York.

10:12.780 --> 10:14.560
A cop, huh?

10:14.580 --> 10:15.940
NYPD Blue.

10:16.000 --> 10:18.200
[LAUGHS] Something like that.

10:20.030 --> 10:22.280
You sure you were just driving by?

10:22.400 --> 10:24.700
Am I free to go, signora?

10:24.780 --> 10:25.800
For now.

10:25.840 --> 10:28.440
Grazie.

10:28.480 --> 10:30.700
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

10:35.870 --> 10:38.200
You know, it would seem, Mr. Ravenzo,

10:38.220 --> 10:42.000
that someone put a hit out on your wife.

10:42.160 --> 10:44.659
What? I don't understand.

10:44.660 --> 10:46.560
Passenger seat belt on your car was cut.

10:46.580 --> 10:48.930
Someone tried to kill her and
make it look like an accident.

10:48.970 --> 10:50.540
Then why was she taken?

10:50.580 --> 10:53.240
Well, the assassins didn't
know who their target was.

10:53.280 --> 10:56.070
When they did, they decided to
cash in on the Ravenzo name.

10:56.080 --> 10:57.840
It was a crime of opportunity.

11:00.900 --> 11:03.620
Uh, are you sure that
your sister's coming?

11:03.630 --> 11:06.080
I called her, sent her a text.

11:06.110 --> 11:08.910
- Giulia is, uh...
- My daughter has an

11:08.950 --> 11:11.950
A-type personality. It's
impossible to get her

11:12.000 --> 11:15.280
to stop doing the things she
loves, and she loves her work.

11:15.340 --> 11:17.160
Ever since she was little, she...

11:17.170 --> 11:20.380
She has been a heartless bitch.

11:21.080 --> 11:23.500
FRANCESCA: Sandro is head of marketing,

11:23.520 --> 11:26.220
but Giulia is the chief
operations officer.

11:26.240 --> 11:27.520
And you're CEO?

11:27.580 --> 11:29.426
I've taken a step back with age.

11:29.427 --> 11:30.840
It's Giulia's company now.

11:31.840 --> 11:35.560
Uh, Mr. Ravenzo, I-I know this
is hard, but I have to ask.

11:35.620 --> 11:38.300
Who would want your wife dead?

11:38.340 --> 11:39.420
I have no idea.

11:39.440 --> 11:43.720
Fiona is well-liked, a philanthropist.

11:43.770 --> 11:45.639
She spent more time with
our factory workers

11:45.640 --> 11:46.900
than the fashion elite.

11:46.940 --> 11:48.060
She is kind.

11:48.090 --> 11:51.080
That someone would try to
kill her, doesn't make sense.

11:51.140 --> 11:52.540
Who's Roberto Ferrucci?

11:52.550 --> 11:53.660
Why do you ask?

11:54.640 --> 11:57.060
I found a restraining order online.

11:57.120 --> 11:58.900
It was filed by Fiona

11:58.920 --> 12:00.700
against a Roberto Ferrucci.

12:00.720 --> 12:03.040
FRANCESCA: Roberto was our old designer.

12:03.050 --> 12:06.140
A hothead like all
artists, but not a killer.

12:06.180 --> 12:08.270
Well, a restraining order
isn't easy to get.

12:08.310 --> 12:11.140
You know, someone had to
think the threat was real,

12:11.180 --> 12:12.279
including a judge.

12:12.280 --> 12:14.480
Roberto worked for our
company for years.

12:14.520 --> 12:16.600
He became infatuated with Fiona.

12:16.680 --> 12:19.440
He stalked her, made
inappropriate comments.

12:19.520 --> 12:21.480
After several warnings, I had him fired.

12:22.660 --> 12:24.590
He made threats.

12:24.630 --> 12:25.990
This is why the restraining order.

12:37.280 --> 12:39.699
Is it just me, or did
Sandro seem nervous

12:39.700 --> 12:41.939
about us talking to his
old buddy, Roberto?

12:41.940 --> 12:43.780
Yeah, I caught that, too.

12:43.800 --> 12:45.560
Find him. If we can prove he's involved,

12:45.580 --> 12:48.300
we might be able to leverage
it with the kidnappers.

12:49.520 --> 12:53.040
See if you can track down
Fiona's life insurance policy.

12:53.080 --> 12:55.279
It'd be good to see who
stands to gain from her death

12:55.280 --> 12:57.040
- and by how much.
- Okay.

12:57.100 --> 13:01.000
Oh, and, um, by the way,

13:01.080 --> 13:02.920
a cop turned up at the crash site.

13:02.950 --> 13:05.220
Good chance they'll be by here soon.

13:05.270 --> 13:09.020
Well, we better get
our stories straight.

13:15.280 --> 13:17.940
My mother does the same
thing when she's worried.

13:17.980 --> 13:20.030
[CHUCKLES]

13:20.120 --> 13:22.120
I have been through a lot.

13:22.170 --> 13:24.660
Was widowed young.

13:24.670 --> 13:26.820
This is just the next thing.

13:26.870 --> 13:29.630
Francesca, the police
found Sandro's car.

13:29.640 --> 13:30.990
It's only a matter of time

13:31.000 --> 13:33.570
before they start asking questions.

13:33.610 --> 13:35.880
The police will not hear
about Fiona from me.

13:38.680 --> 13:41.680
Is this your father?

13:41.860 --> 13:46.020
That is the man who give us all of this,

13:46.060 --> 13:47.580
my grandfather.

13:50.070 --> 13:52.850
We were... [SPEAKS ITALIAN]

13:52.890 --> 13:54.630
Dirt poor.

13:54.640 --> 13:56.330
Something the old money of Florence

13:56.340 --> 13:57.720
never let my father forget.

13:57.860 --> 14:00.060
You must understand, Mr. Beaumont,

14:00.080 --> 14:02.280
our name was all we had.

14:02.340 --> 14:04.910
My father vowed we would
never give it up,

14:04.950 --> 14:06.660
even when I was married.

14:06.680 --> 14:09.540
There is much in a name.

14:09.570 --> 14:12.520
Something my children
have not yet realized.

14:12.650 --> 14:14.140
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

14:14.220 --> 14:15.300
Hello.

14:15.440 --> 14:18.050
Ah, Lorenzo.

14:18.090 --> 14:21.750
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

14:21.790 --> 14:22.840
Third time

14:22.850 --> 14:25.220
in two months Sandro
has crashed the car.

14:25.240 --> 14:27.440
Francesca, the way he treats you.

14:27.470 --> 14:28.620
I'm a police officer.

14:28.630 --> 14:30.519
It is getting harder
to look the other way.

14:30.520 --> 14:32.760
- This is the last time.
- Of course.

14:32.800 --> 14:34.480
It's always the last time.

14:34.500 --> 14:37.980
Come. Come. Sit.

14:38.030 --> 14:40.060
And you are?

14:40.100 --> 14:43.099
Eric Beaumont. Uh, I'm a negotiator.

14:43.100 --> 14:45.030
Negotiator?

14:46.780 --> 14:49.319
The Ravenzos have business
that's extremely time-sensitive.

14:49.320 --> 14:50.910
My team flew in to
guide them through it.

14:50.950 --> 14:53.740
You flew in? Big shot, huh?

14:53.760 --> 14:55.080
Just a helping hand.

14:56.060 --> 14:58.580
Okay, well, I'm gonna leave you to it.

15:02.480 --> 15:04.520
CYNTHIA: Mr. Ferrucci,
we just want to ask you

15:04.580 --> 15:06.959
- a couple of questions.
- No, I'm on my way to a meeting

15:06.960 --> 15:08.719
and have no desire to ruin my day

15:08.720 --> 15:11.380
by talking about that
damn Ravenzo. Capisce?

15:11.390 --> 15:13.399
Well, someone tried to
kill Fiona Ravenzo,

15:13.400 --> 15:15.410
and since there's a restraining
order out against you,

15:15.450 --> 15:17.890
I think that makes you a
solid suspect. Capisce?

15:17.930 --> 15:19.190
What?

15:19.200 --> 15:21.240
We just want to know where
you were last night.

15:21.280 --> 15:24.420
[LAUGHING]: No, no, no. You
should be looking at Sandro.

15:24.460 --> 15:26.420
He and Fiona are always fighting.

15:26.440 --> 15:30.330
Protecting the precious Ravenzo
name is his only priority.

15:30.380 --> 15:33.420
That a weasel like him could
steal a woman from me.

15:33.470 --> 15:35.730
- Wait, steal?
- Yes.

15:35.770 --> 15:37.950
Fiona was my girlfriend first.

15:37.990 --> 15:40.300
Then Sandro somehow seduced her away.

15:40.340 --> 15:42.259
I'm not surprised he neglected

15:42.260 --> 15:43.699
to mention that part.

15:43.700 --> 15:45.440
When you said Sandro's only priority

15:45.480 --> 15:47.790
was to protect the Ravenzo
name, what'd you mean by that?

15:47.830 --> 15:50.440
Okay, enough. I got to go.

15:50.490 --> 15:51.960
- I'm done talking to...
- Listen, Roberto.

15:51.970 --> 15:53.420
Out of my way.

15:54.600 --> 15:56.900
How about you give us a call

15:56.910 --> 15:58.320
if your blood pressure drops

15:58.360 --> 16:00.930
and you suddenly remember something?

16:08.940 --> 16:10.460
KIDNAPPER: Do you have the money?

16:10.520 --> 16:12.720
We were able to get the half
million euros discussed.

16:12.740 --> 16:14.460
Now, if you give us the
location, we'll make the...

16:14.470 --> 16:16.470
KIDNAPPER: Half million is not enough.

16:16.510 --> 16:18.760
It was enough earlier. What's changed?

16:18.860 --> 16:20.650
I think she's worth more.

16:20.690 --> 16:23.040
Unless you have a better
offer, I hang up.

16:23.080 --> 16:24.690
You have to give us more time.

16:24.700 --> 16:26.920
No more time. We are done.

16:26.960 --> 16:28.390
I can get you one million euros.

16:29.870 --> 16:33.090
Finally a serious offer.

16:33.100 --> 16:35.830
Stay by the phone. Wait for our call.

16:35.880 --> 16:36.920
[BEEP]

16:36.930 --> 16:38.120
Does it bother you that we keep

16:38.140 --> 16:40.060
going up in price in this negotiation?

16:40.080 --> 16:41.669
We usually talk them down.

16:41.670 --> 16:44.140
But they said, "Unless you
have a better offer."

16:44.200 --> 16:46.020
So?

16:46.060 --> 16:49.040
So whoever paid these men to
kill Fiona are still in play.

16:49.050 --> 16:51.020
The kidnappers are taking
offers from both sides.

16:51.070 --> 16:52.320
We're in a bidding war.

16:52.460 --> 16:55.780
And whoever pays the most
money first, gets Fiona.

16:55.820 --> 16:57.940
Dead or alive.

17:03.560 --> 17:04.740
ZARA: Sandro,

17:04.780 --> 17:06.359
where's your mother?

17:06.380 --> 17:08.959
Lying down. The stress of
this thing is too much.

17:08.960 --> 17:10.160
Your sister?

17:10.170 --> 17:11.770
Fiona isn't made of leather,

17:11.780 --> 17:13.279
so don't count on Giulia being here.

17:13.280 --> 17:15.010
How much money can you get quickly?

17:15.050 --> 17:16.619
You just promised them a million.

17:16.630 --> 17:18.378
They may have already
received a better offer.

17:18.380 --> 17:19.740
You really believe someone would pay

17:19.750 --> 17:21.479
over a million euro to kill my wife?

17:21.480 --> 17:23.699
I don't know, but we have
to be prepared to bid

17:23.700 --> 17:25.630
until their revenue stream is exhausted.

17:25.670 --> 17:29.330
- So how much can you get?
- I'll talk to the bank.

17:29.370 --> 17:31.200
Thank you.

17:32.290 --> 17:33.590
CYNTHIA: Eric.

17:33.600 --> 17:34.860
What's happening with Roberto?

17:34.880 --> 17:37.320
He blew us off, threatened
us, then he sent us a text.

17:37.350 --> 17:39.550
It says, "You want the truth?

17:39.600 --> 17:41.290
Here's a time and a place to meet."

17:41.340 --> 17:43.400
You don't like the look of
the place, you don't go in.

17:43.460 --> 17:45.600
We're about preserving
lives, our own included.

17:48.740 --> 17:50.610
Any luck with Fiona's life insurance?

17:50.650 --> 17:51.870
Waiting for a call.

17:53.390 --> 17:56.090
Pay Giulia a visit in the meantime.

17:56.140 --> 17:58.750
See why she hasn't been with the
family in this time of need.

17:58.790 --> 17:59.900
Something tells me this isn't

17:59.920 --> 18:01.710
your garden variety family feuding.

18:01.750 --> 18:03.010
What about you?

18:03.060 --> 18:06.020
I think it's time to come
clean to the police.

18:06.100 --> 18:08.710
[BELL CHIMING]

18:08.760 --> 18:11.700
That's why they are so
expensive, Ms. Hallam.

18:11.720 --> 18:14.140
Handcrafted by real artisans.

18:14.200 --> 18:16.240
The mark of true Italian quality.

18:16.270 --> 18:18.240
Mm.

18:18.290 --> 18:20.770
They're lovely.

18:20.810 --> 18:22.770
I'm very sorry for not coming by.

18:22.810 --> 18:25.920
I can only imagine what
Sandro must be going through.

18:26.000 --> 18:28.440
But we have put everything
in this new bag,

18:28.470 --> 18:30.560
and someone has to
oversee the deliveries.

18:30.580 --> 18:33.840
Fiona's kidnapping could not
have come at a worse time.

18:34.000 --> 18:36.610
Please, don't mistake my
devotion for the Ravenzo legacy

18:36.650 --> 18:38.860
as a lack of concern
for my brother's wife.

18:38.960 --> 18:41.539
What should I mistake it as?

18:41.540 --> 18:44.820
My mother and Sandro are on
the board of the company.

18:44.850 --> 18:48.920
They have fancy titles, but
if I left everything to them,

18:48.960 --> 18:51.930
the company would fall to ruin.

18:51.970 --> 18:54.199
I'm busy. Is that a crime?

18:54.200 --> 18:57.500
No. I guess the optics
just aren't great.

18:57.540 --> 18:58.980
If I didn't know better, I'd think...

18:59.020 --> 19:01.200
Sandro and Fiona have
been fighting for months.

19:01.290 --> 19:03.900
A week ago, I was working late

19:03.920 --> 19:05.840
and I went out for a meal.

19:05.940 --> 19:08.340
I saw Fiona and her ex, Roberto.

19:08.440 --> 19:11.960
Whispering, talking close.

19:12.000 --> 19:13.899
Throw a rock, and you will hit 20 women

19:13.900 --> 19:15.900
that dreamed of marrying my brother,

19:15.940 --> 19:17.380
marry my family,

19:17.400 --> 19:19.350
but not Fiona.

19:19.390 --> 19:21.720
Fiona resented us.

19:21.870 --> 19:24.620
So what are you suggesting?

19:27.020 --> 19:30.400
I think Fiona has conspired
with Roberto to kidnap herself.

19:30.450 --> 19:33.720
But if she was unhappy,
she could have just left.

19:33.740 --> 19:35.020
Why take the risk?

19:35.190 --> 19:37.280
The family money's tied up in a trust.

19:37.300 --> 19:39.519
If she divorces my
brother, she gets nothing.

19:39.520 --> 19:42.040
Everyone else wants what we have.

19:42.080 --> 19:44.080
Why should she be so different?

19:50.580 --> 19:54.699
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

19:54.700 --> 19:56.600
MAN: What are you doing?

20:00.320 --> 20:02.440
[INDISTINCT ARGUMENT]

20:12.220 --> 20:14.000
MAN: What are you doing?

20:22.640 --> 20:25.140
CYNTHIA: Are you sure this is
where Roberto said to meet?

20:25.220 --> 20:27.600
[COUGHS]

20:27.640 --> 20:29.860
Yep. This is it.

20:29.880 --> 20:31.700
Roberto. Hello?

20:31.710 --> 20:33.400
If this is Roberto's idea of a date,

20:33.410 --> 20:35.860
I'm starting to see why Fiona left him.

20:35.900 --> 20:38.840
According to Google Maps,
this was a Ravenzo factory.

20:38.900 --> 20:41.129
Press release said it
burned down a month ago.

20:41.130 --> 20:42.690
Threatened the launch of the new bag.

20:42.740 --> 20:45.000
Timing of that smells an
awful lot like arson.

20:45.040 --> 20:49.120
Fire makes a bag more
exclusive, aka more expensive.

20:49.140 --> 20:52.360
- You really want one, huh?
- [LAUGHING]: Oh, that.

20:52.380 --> 20:55.100
First time I saw a Ravenzo, it
was in a celebrity magazine.

20:55.120 --> 20:57.720
I was about eight. I was obsessed.

20:57.740 --> 20:59.720
So where is he?

20:59.940 --> 21:01.760
[COUGHS]

21:02.820 --> 21:06.700
- Cynthia.
- What? Oh.

21:06.780 --> 21:09.380
- [FLIES BUZZING]
- Looks like a bull

21:09.400 --> 21:11.590
or an ox or some...

21:11.630 --> 21:13.330
- [GROANS]
- [COUGHS]

21:13.380 --> 21:15.550
Shine your light right here.

21:15.600 --> 21:18.030
Looks like some sort of sacrifice.

21:18.080 --> 21:19.820
[CAMERA CLICKS]

21:19.860 --> 21:22.840
- Okay.
- Okay, let's go.

21:22.880 --> 21:24.340
[COUGHING]

21:31.520 --> 21:33.480
Peace offering.

21:33.530 --> 21:35.540
That's not going to be enough.

21:37.620 --> 21:40.450
A negotiator of kidnappings.

21:42.540 --> 21:44.380
I wasn't entirely truthful

21:44.400 --> 21:46.020
when you visited the Ravenzos earlier.

21:46.060 --> 21:47.150
You don't say.

21:47.190 --> 21:48.670
Fiona's been taken.

21:50.330 --> 21:52.200
Fiona is a good woman.

21:52.240 --> 21:53.810
Too good for a man like Sandro.

21:53.850 --> 21:55.500
You know the Ravenzos well, don't you?

21:55.550 --> 21:57.860
Everyone in Italy knows
the Ravenzos well.

21:57.900 --> 22:00.470
When you came by the house,
I noticed a closeness

22:00.510 --> 22:02.820
between you and Francesca.

22:02.860 --> 22:04.990
Maternal, even.

22:06.990 --> 22:09.700
The Ravenzos took my family
in after World War II.

22:09.800 --> 22:12.080
When everyone was
starving and destitute,

22:12.170 --> 22:14.310
the Ravenzos gave my grandparents work,

22:14.350 --> 22:16.480
a place to live.

22:16.530 --> 22:20.010
And when my parents died,
Francesca took me in

22:20.050 --> 22:22.480
and raised me alongside
her own children.

22:22.540 --> 22:24.760
The woman is a saint.

22:24.880 --> 22:29.280
But I was alive for the Brigate Rosse.

22:29.300 --> 22:31.150
I watched as they extorted

22:31.190 --> 22:33.330
the privileged of our
country for ransom.

22:33.370 --> 22:35.280
Held our government hostage.

22:35.300 --> 22:39.330
This type of negotiation
was banned for a reason.

22:39.370 --> 22:41.940
But you've seen my website.
You know what I can do.

22:43.220 --> 22:45.340
With your help, we can ensure
this stays out of the press.

22:45.350 --> 22:48.800
Nobody knows except my team,
the Ravenzos and you.

22:50.560 --> 22:52.300
Hypothetically,

22:52.340 --> 22:54.420
if I were to look the other way...

22:56.440 --> 22:58.179
... what other way would I look?

22:58.180 --> 23:01.120
I need you to do full
forensics on Sandro's car.

23:01.140 --> 23:05.140
Fingerprints, DNA, the works,
and if this was a hit,

23:05.180 --> 23:07.120
now it's an auction for Fiona's life.

23:07.140 --> 23:09.190
If we lose the bid,
identifying the kidnappers,

23:09.230 --> 23:11.280
tracking them down, may
be the only way for us

23:11.320 --> 23:12.680
to bring Fiona back alive.

23:12.720 --> 23:14.400
I'll call you when it's ready.

23:14.410 --> 23:16.930
Okay, thank you.

23:16.940 --> 23:18.960
Mr. Beaumont.

23:20.980 --> 23:25.120
If you in any way take advantage
of Francesca Ravenzo,

23:25.160 --> 23:28.550
being arrested for negotiating ransom

23:28.600 --> 23:30.730
will be the least of your problems.

23:41.760 --> 23:44.000
Hey.

23:44.050 --> 23:46.200
How much did you get?

23:46.220 --> 23:48.360
None.

23:48.400 --> 23:51.060
The million I got earlier
emptied the family trust.

23:51.100 --> 23:52.540
There is no more.

23:52.550 --> 23:55.099
Well, I find it hard to believe
the Ravenzo fashion empire...

23:55.100 --> 23:56.760
What, do you think we are made of money?

23:56.770 --> 23:58.410
Huh?

23:58.450 --> 23:59.480
Is that it?

24:00.980 --> 24:03.019
This new bag, the overhead,

24:03.020 --> 24:05.439
the deliveries, you have no idea.

24:05.440 --> 24:07.270
Ravenzo Luxury Goods is worth a fortune.

24:07.280 --> 24:09.579
I mean, the name alone could
sell for what? Half a billion.

24:09.580 --> 24:11.580
What's going on, Sandro?
Where's the money?

24:12.340 --> 24:13.760
I lost it.

24:14.720 --> 24:16.210
Gambling.

24:17.980 --> 24:20.140
I kept thinking I could win it back

24:20.150 --> 24:22.090
and refill the trust
before anyone noticed,

24:22.130 --> 24:24.020
but I kept losing,

24:24.040 --> 24:26.420
and no bank will touch me now.

24:28.610 --> 24:30.440
You think it's me.

24:30.490 --> 24:31.680
[PHONE RINGING]

24:31.880 --> 24:34.800
You think I did this to my wife.

24:35.010 --> 24:37.040
I love Fiona.

24:37.190 --> 24:39.190
I have to take this.

24:42.440 --> 24:43.560
Oliver.

24:43.600 --> 24:45.000
OLIVER [OVER PHONE]:
Roberto was a no-show,

24:45.020 --> 24:47.399
so we decided to knock
for him at his shop.

24:47.400 --> 24:48.460
And?

24:48.500 --> 24:50.940
He's dead.

24:50.980 --> 24:52.520
CYNTHIA: Suicide.

24:52.550 --> 24:55.080
Either that or a murder made
to look like one. Anyway,

24:55.120 --> 24:56.180
police are on their way.

24:56.190 --> 24:57.352
Okay, get back here when you're done.

24:57.353 --> 24:58.400
Get me a statement.

25:00.950 --> 25:02.000
What's going on there?

25:03.430 --> 25:06.040
Were you able to track down
a life insurance policy?

25:06.090 --> 25:08.920
Yeah. Ten million euros.

25:08.960 --> 25:10.480
To who?

25:11.460 --> 25:13.880
The Ravenzo family trust.

25:28.590 --> 25:30.370
Well, Giulia's finally arrived.

25:30.420 --> 25:32.550
She's in the study, working.

25:32.590 --> 25:34.999
Francesca and Sandro are in the kitchen.

25:35.000 --> 25:36.860
Do we really think one of the Ravenzos

25:36.900 --> 25:38.210
is trying to have Fiona killed?

25:38.250 --> 25:39.940
ERIC: Her insurance pays ten million

25:39.960 --> 25:41.540
to the Ravenzo family trust.

25:41.550 --> 25:42.819
Nothing else makes sense.

25:42.820 --> 25:44.740
So if the Ravenzos are our clients,

25:44.780 --> 25:47.040
that means we're in a bidding
war against ourselves.

25:47.090 --> 25:48.350
Yeah, it looks that way.

25:48.390 --> 25:50.400
So? Which Ravenzo is it?

25:50.410 --> 25:52.679
Well, I don't see Francesca
risking her son's life

25:52.680 --> 25:54.040
just to kill his wife.

25:54.080 --> 25:55.740
My vote's for Giulia.

25:55.800 --> 25:57.980
This is the first time
she's been to the house

25:58.000 --> 25:59.270
since Fiona was taken.

25:59.320 --> 26:01.120
CYNTHIA: If the factory fire was arson,

26:01.140 --> 26:02.739
we can assume that Roberto knew...

26:02.740 --> 26:06.780
that's why he led us there...
but what if Fiona knew as well?

26:06.840 --> 26:10.139
Giulia showed me a photograph
of Fiona and Roberto together.

26:10.140 --> 26:11.799
Now, she thought they
were having an affair,

26:11.800 --> 26:14.900
but what if he was telling
her what he found out?

26:14.980 --> 26:16.400
That's when she confronted Giulia,

26:16.410 --> 26:18.279
Giulia puts a hit out on Fiona

26:18.280 --> 26:20.680
to shut her up about the arson.

26:20.900 --> 26:24.520
Makes you wonder what else
these people are capable of.

26:26.470 --> 26:29.260
We're sure that Roberto
wasn't a suicide, right?

26:29.280 --> 26:32.020
Nah, nah. Right when he's
about to blow the whistle

26:32.040 --> 26:34.859
on the Ravenzos for burning
down their own factory,

26:34.860 --> 26:36.790
he takes his own life?

26:36.830 --> 26:39.100
That's too coincidental.

26:39.140 --> 26:41.899
If we're gonna accuse the
people picking up our tab

26:41.900 --> 26:44.100
of murder, I'd really
like to be certain.

26:44.140 --> 26:46.360
Okay, head to the police station.

26:46.380 --> 26:48.240
See if you can get eyes
on that forensics report

26:48.280 --> 26:49.400
from the cop that you met.

26:49.410 --> 26:51.160
S.I. Marmoldo didn't come through?

26:51.170 --> 26:53.439
He practically threatened to
kill me if I touched a hair

26:53.440 --> 26:54.469
on Francesca's head.

26:54.470 --> 26:56.850
Now, if he catches on that
we're about to accuse

26:56.900 --> 26:58.030
a member of her family,

26:58.070 --> 26:59.760
we may never see that report.

26:59.770 --> 27:02.850
It's our only contingency
if we get outbid.

27:02.880 --> 27:05.560
- I'll be in touch.
- Thanks.

27:05.770 --> 27:07.320
What about that dead ox?

27:07.340 --> 27:09.520
On the way to interview the
man that purchased it now.

27:09.550 --> 27:10.620
Let me know what you find,

27:10.630 --> 27:13.820
if it has anything to
do with Giulia Ravenzo.

27:13.840 --> 27:15.360
I am very interested to see

27:15.370 --> 27:17.870
how she behaves during the next call.

27:21.200 --> 27:23.780
Please, a woman's life is at stake.

27:23.800 --> 27:25.680
I can't talk to you. I'm working.

27:25.700 --> 27:28.970
But you did buy the ox, right?
Look, I have the invoice.

27:29.010 --> 27:30.450
I don't want any trouble.

27:30.490 --> 27:33.460
Just tell me why you killed
that ox, and I will leave.

27:33.470 --> 27:35.150
I don't have papers.

27:35.200 --> 27:37.020
My family, they depend on me.

27:37.070 --> 27:40.040
Look, this woman's life's at stake.

27:42.440 --> 27:43.780
You know Fiona, don't you?

27:43.840 --> 27:46.560
She's kind. Not like the other Ravenzos.

27:46.580 --> 27:49.340
Someone's trying to kill her, Gogo.

27:49.540 --> 27:53.160
Just tell me what you know,
it could save her life.

27:54.120 --> 27:57.200
Time's up. How much can you do?

27:57.260 --> 27:59.060
We don't have any more money.

27:59.080 --> 28:01.060
- Then we are done.
- Why?

28:01.070 --> 28:02.879
Because you received a better
offer from whoever hired you

28:02.880 --> 28:04.440
to kill Fiona?

28:04.460 --> 28:05.939
What's the number?

28:05.940 --> 28:08.599
One and a quarter million euros.

28:08.600 --> 28:11.020
How much of that money do you
think you'll live to spend?

28:11.040 --> 28:13.220
I am not interested in what-ifs.

28:13.240 --> 28:15.580
I'm interested in getting paid.

28:15.640 --> 28:17.540
He's serious, Eric.

28:17.590 --> 28:19.320
We need to make an offer,
or he's gonna kill Fiona.

28:19.340 --> 28:22.480
Well, we don't have
anything to offer. Do we?

28:25.420 --> 28:28.199
Giulia, aiutami.

28:28.200 --> 28:29.700
Please.

28:29.760 --> 28:31.020
Aiutarti?

28:31.100 --> 28:32.900
- Sì.
- Sì?

28:32.980 --> 28:34.599
Like you helped the company?

28:34.600 --> 28:37.380
But Fiona didn't do that. I did.

28:37.390 --> 28:38.480
Look.

28:38.520 --> 28:40.940
Look at this. How do you know Fiona

28:40.960 --> 28:42.960
isn't behind this herself?

28:43.000 --> 28:44.580
How dare you?

28:44.600 --> 28:46.860
Are you really going to let her die?

28:46.900 --> 28:48.520
I screwed up.

28:48.530 --> 28:51.020
But don't punish Fiona
for my mistakes, please.

28:52.380 --> 28:54.120
Giulia, I got to give him an answer.

28:54.180 --> 28:56.220
I will do anything you ask.

28:59.820 --> 29:01.370
Okay.

29:01.410 --> 29:02.600
I will get the money.

29:03.840 --> 29:06.470
Tell them 1.5 million euros,

29:06.480 --> 29:07.820
and not a penny more.

29:08.700 --> 29:10.920
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

29:10.990 --> 29:13.250
I have 1.5 million euro.

29:13.300 --> 29:15.430
You won't do better.

29:17.790 --> 29:19.700
We accept.

29:19.750 --> 29:21.530
- [EXHALES]
- There is a phone

29:21.570 --> 29:25.060
under a white rock about a
hundred yards down the road.

29:25.100 --> 29:27.360
Drive north with the money,

29:27.410 --> 29:30.320
and we will give you further directions.

29:36.940 --> 29:40.680
[PHONE RINGING]

29:40.720 --> 29:42.070
Anything?

29:42.120 --> 29:43.770
ZARA [OVER PHONE]: Hey,
Eric, I'm here with Elisa.

29:43.810 --> 29:47.300
No fingerprints in the
report, no DNA, no trace.

29:47.310 --> 29:48.639
Zara, check and see if there's

29:48.640 --> 29:50.279
any mention of the tampered seat belt.

29:50.280 --> 29:51.290
Hang on.

29:53.470 --> 29:54.950
No.

29:55.000 --> 29:57.020
No mention of the seat belt, either.

29:57.040 --> 30:00.480
Yes, there is. I filled
out the report myself.

30:00.560 --> 30:02.860
This is not my work.

30:02.910 --> 30:04.430
This is a fake.

30:04.470 --> 30:05.820
Who faked the report?

30:09.740 --> 30:13.350
Station Inspector Lorenzo Marmoldo.

30:18.710 --> 30:21.010
Mr. Beaumont.

30:21.060 --> 30:22.640
I must insist I take over.

30:25.580 --> 30:28.139
- Inspector Marmoldo, I don't understand...
- I know it is not ideal,

30:28.140 --> 30:29.540
but it would be better for me.

30:29.590 --> 30:31.820
My career. You understand.

30:31.860 --> 30:32.959
I think we both know your career

30:32.960 --> 30:35.160
- is in enough trouble already.
- Excuse me?

30:35.200 --> 30:37.680
Been right under my nose since
I got here, but now I see.

30:37.730 --> 30:39.070
It wasn't Giulia.

30:39.120 --> 30:41.420
I know what you and Francesca are up to.

30:41.470 --> 30:43.990
I have no idea what you are insinuating.

30:44.040 --> 30:47.640
I'm insinuating that Francesca
didn't raise you like a son.

30:47.660 --> 30:49.060
She raised you like an attack dog.

30:50.420 --> 30:53.440
You think she'd risk her
own blood to kill Roberto?

30:53.480 --> 30:55.820
Fiona? Start the fire?

30:55.920 --> 30:58.660
[LAUGHS SOFTLY]

31:00.040 --> 31:03.320
I'm going to collect Fiona Ravenzo

31:03.340 --> 31:04.670
and bring her back home.

31:04.710 --> 31:05.840
If I were you,

31:05.880 --> 31:07.940
I would not be here when I get back.

31:09.890 --> 31:11.659
Here you go.

31:11.660 --> 31:14.740
The phone the kidnappers left for us.

31:29.520 --> 31:31.340
[ENGINE STARTS]

31:36.390 --> 31:39.180
Hey. What's up? Where's the money?

31:39.200 --> 31:41.620
Lorenzo has it.

31:41.630 --> 31:43.699
And unless we can wrestle
the leash from Francesca,

31:43.700 --> 31:46.710
he's gonna kill Fiona
and the kidnappers.

31:46.750 --> 31:48.930
No loose ends.

31:51.590 --> 31:53.900
OLIVER: You're positive
it's Francesca and Lorenzo?

31:53.950 --> 31:56.540
Lorenzo's sure risking
a lot to help her.

31:56.570 --> 31:58.820
The Ravenzos took his family in.
They raised him like a son.

31:58.860 --> 32:01.000
I mean, he was a... he was a
nobody who became part of

32:01.040 --> 32:02.480
one of the greatest
dynasties in this country.

32:02.520 --> 32:06.090
A feeling of indebtedness
is a very strong motivator.

32:06.130 --> 32:09.180
It's possible Lorenzo would do
anything to please Francesca.

32:09.220 --> 32:10.440
CYNTHIA: The Nguni migrant

32:10.480 --> 32:12.700
who bought the ox... I got him to talk.

32:12.750 --> 32:14.219
The Ravenzos burned

32:14.220 --> 32:16.530
a lot more than bags in that fire.

32:19.320 --> 32:20.930
Any word?

32:20.970 --> 32:22.540
About the conspiracy to commit murder?

32:22.580 --> 32:24.519
Excuse me?

32:24.520 --> 32:26.440
You burned the factory down.

32:26.480 --> 32:29.419
You put the hit out on Fiona,
had Lorenzo kill Roberto,

32:29.420 --> 32:31.440
and now he's gone to
finish the job on Fiona.

32:31.460 --> 32:34.260
- I mean, is that it?
- Uh, Mr. Beaumont, what are you saying?

32:34.270 --> 32:36.600
That night you saw Roberto
and Fiona talking,

32:36.610 --> 32:38.519
he was telling her about
the arson, how Lorenzo

32:38.520 --> 32:40.899
burned down the factory
for the insurance money.

32:40.900 --> 32:42.260
Fiona confronted you,

32:42.300 --> 32:44.470
and that's why you tried
to have her killed.

32:44.520 --> 32:45.870
Why would my mother do something...

32:45.880 --> 32:47.740
I spoke to a man named Gogo.

32:47.780 --> 32:51.559
Two of your Nguni migrant
workers died in that fire.

32:51.560 --> 32:52.840
They were his cousins.

32:52.850 --> 32:55.279
We found Gogo because
he sacrificed an ox

32:55.280 --> 32:56.399
at the factory.

32:56.400 --> 32:57.980
It's a Nguni tradition.

32:58.100 --> 32:59.799
You said it yourself, Sandro.

32:59.800 --> 33:01.880
Fiona spent more time
with the factory workers

33:01.930 --> 33:03.280
than the fashion elite.

33:03.320 --> 33:04.780
She was friends with them.

33:04.930 --> 33:06.450
You knew she'd never
keep quiet about it,

33:06.500 --> 33:07.890
so you tried to have her killed.

33:07.930 --> 33:10.530
Only problem was, she took Sandro's car

33:10.540 --> 33:13.680
at the launch, drove herself home.

33:13.720 --> 33:16.200
She didn't die in the crash,
like you planned, did she?

33:17.380 --> 33:20.210
- [SPEAKS ITALIAN]
- Shut up!

33:20.250 --> 33:23.020
Mr. Beaumont,

33:23.030 --> 33:25.680
I don't know what you are
talking about, but...

33:25.750 --> 33:27.980
if Lorenzo is, as you say he is,

33:28.000 --> 33:32.500
a bad apple, you have
already run out of time.

33:32.560 --> 33:35.700
Unless Zara can track
him on my cell phone.

33:35.740 --> 33:38.280
Put it in the bag with the money.

33:41.760 --> 33:43.660
[PHONE RINGING]

33:43.710 --> 33:44.899
Hey.

33:44.900 --> 33:47.520
- We're two minutes behind him.
- [SPEAKS ITALIAN]

33:47.550 --> 33:49.000
All right, tell us when
you've caught up to him.

33:49.020 --> 33:50.160
Copy that.

33:55.080 --> 33:56.360
[BOTH GRUNT]

33:56.440 --> 33:58.360
[TIRES SCREECHING]

34:00.880 --> 34:02.120
Zara, talk to me.

34:02.160 --> 34:04.160
[PANTING]

34:06.460 --> 34:09.219
Sorry, Eric. Looks like Lorenzo

34:09.230 --> 34:10.860
didn't want anyone to follow him.

34:10.949 --> 34:14.420
Lorenzo has always been a smart boy.

34:14.440 --> 34:15.879
Smarter than most.

34:15.880 --> 34:17.940
You told me the workers were removed.

34:17.960 --> 34:20.199
Why didn't you move the
migrants like we agreed?

34:20.210 --> 34:22.639
They could have said something
to the insurance company.

34:22.659 --> 34:24.179
CYNTHIA: They were no threat to you.

34:24.199 --> 34:26.139
They were in this country illegally.

34:26.170 --> 34:27.560
They didn't want any trouble.

34:27.580 --> 34:28.850
You didn't have them moved

34:28.880 --> 34:30.380
because you didn't see them as people.

34:30.400 --> 34:32.179
You saw them as an acceptable loss.

34:32.199 --> 34:34.020
ERIC: There's only one way
out of this, Francesca.

34:34.040 --> 34:36.149
I know the hold you have over Lorenzo.

34:36.150 --> 34:38.340
Only you can call him off, so do it.

34:39.810 --> 34:41.109
What?

34:41.110 --> 34:42.780
No.

34:50.000 --> 34:52.080
[GUNS CLICKING]

34:53.480 --> 34:54.659
Drop the money.

35:09.710 --> 35:11.490
It's good.

35:11.500 --> 35:12.760
Where is she?

35:12.770 --> 35:14.320
She is in the building.

35:27.220 --> 35:28.979
What the hell is this?

35:28.980 --> 35:31.030
- [GUN FIRES]
- [YELLS]

35:46.480 --> 35:48.270
Mama.

35:49.220 --> 35:51.180
Was I an acceptable loss?

35:51.230 --> 35:54.140
I was supposed to be driving this car.

35:54.190 --> 35:56.450
However, it worked out.

35:56.490 --> 35:58.200
We planned it so you'd live.

35:58.220 --> 35:59.980
So be grateful, because you have

35:59.990 --> 36:04.240
done nothing but take, take
and take your entire life.

36:04.260 --> 36:06.780
It was time to get back.

36:08.220 --> 36:12.260
All we have ever done
was try to please you.

36:12.320 --> 36:15.690
But you prefer Lorenzo,
the gardener's son.

36:15.730 --> 36:17.249
Lorenzo is loyal.

36:17.250 --> 36:19.500
He knows the value of our name.

36:19.560 --> 36:22.220
You value nothing.

36:23.160 --> 36:26.219
Fiona wanted to leave.

36:26.220 --> 36:28.279
She begged me. She begged!

36:28.280 --> 36:30.319
She was going to destroy everything,

36:30.320 --> 36:32.830
everything this family
has worked to build

36:32.880 --> 36:34.419
for over a century.

36:34.420 --> 36:36.850
We survived Mussolini, the
Communists, Berlusconi,

36:36.860 --> 36:39.860
and I was supposed to sit back and watch

36:39.920 --> 36:41.499
as that American puttana

36:41.500 --> 36:44.240
you let in tore everything down?

36:44.280 --> 36:48.450
My father entrusted his name
and this company to me.

36:48.460 --> 36:50.899
ERIC: And there is still a
chance to save the Ravenzo name.

36:50.900 --> 36:52.380
CYNTHIA: No one has
to know about Giulia,

36:52.390 --> 36:54.510
that she knew that the
migrants were squatting there.

36:54.550 --> 36:56.460
She was told that they were
moved, and she believed you.

36:56.470 --> 36:57.499
OLIVER: And we don't need to tell anyone

36:57.500 --> 36:58.840
she was involved with the arson.

36:58.990 --> 37:00.340
ERIC: Call it off.

37:00.380 --> 37:01.920
There's still time.

37:08.170 --> 37:10.060
LORENZO: Fiona, I'm here!

37:14.680 --> 37:16.360
Let's get you home.

37:17.500 --> 37:19.520
[PANTING]

37:23.060 --> 37:25.060
ERIC: If the Ravenzo name

37:25.070 --> 37:26.100
is all you care about,

37:26.160 --> 37:28.380
call Lorenzo off.

37:28.400 --> 37:31.180
He will only listen to you.

37:31.260 --> 37:32.719
Do it.

37:32.720 --> 37:35.920
Or help me, God, I will turn
this company to ash myself.

37:36.680 --> 37:39.060
[GRUNTS]

37:39.120 --> 37:40.180
Hey. [GRUNTS]

37:41.210 --> 37:42.519
Roberto told me

37:42.520 --> 37:45.740
you started the factory fire
that killed those migrants.

37:47.060 --> 37:49.560
[GRUNTING]

37:54.580 --> 37:56.579
ERIC: If you kill Sandro's wife,

37:56.580 --> 37:59.090
the entire Ravenzo empire is gone.

37:59.140 --> 38:00.600
Overnight, like it never existed.

38:00.620 --> 38:04.620
Now, you pick up that phone,
and you call Lorenzo,

38:04.730 --> 38:06.430
Now.

38:14.050 --> 38:16.020
[GRUNTS, WHIMPERS]

38:17.840 --> 38:18.979
- [GUN CLICKS]
- No, no, no.

38:18.980 --> 38:21.150
- [PHONE RINGING]
- Please.

38:22.330 --> 38:24.370
Francesca.

38:24.420 --> 38:25.850
Let Fiona go.

38:25.900 --> 38:27.200
What are you talking about?

38:27.250 --> 38:28.680
We are exposed.

38:28.700 --> 38:30.730
My children have turned on me.

38:30.770 --> 38:33.560
That's what I get for
being kind to them.

38:33.600 --> 38:34.910
Let Fiona go.

38:34.950 --> 38:37.219
It will only make things worse

38:37.220 --> 38:38.600
to kill her now.

38:38.650 --> 38:40.000
What will happen to you?

38:40.040 --> 38:43.040
I will go to jail. I will die there.

38:43.090 --> 38:44.740
[EXHALES]

38:48.660 --> 38:51.050
[PANTING]

38:51.100 --> 38:52.880
I'm sorry.

38:52.920 --> 38:55.010
I'm sorry I let you down.

38:55.020 --> 38:56.670
It's all right, Lorenzo.

38:58.150 --> 39:01.580
It is I who failed my father...

39:03.630 --> 39:07.240
... by trusting any of you.

39:11.720 --> 39:14.030
[SLAMS PHONE ON TABLE]

39:34.140 --> 39:37.100
I'm sorry I never told
you what I found out.

39:37.110 --> 39:38.580
Don't be sorry.

39:38.620 --> 39:41.010
You were worried I wouldn't
have done anything.

39:41.060 --> 39:43.060
You were probably right.

39:44.670 --> 39:46.800
I'm going to get help.

39:46.850 --> 39:50.280
The drinking, the gambling,
I'm done with all this.

39:50.330 --> 39:52.420
I want to start over.

39:56.120 --> 39:58.860
ZARA: Lorenzo's been taken into custody.

40:00.100 --> 40:02.919
Everything Francesca
was trying to protect,

40:02.920 --> 40:04.430
she destroyed.

40:04.470 --> 40:06.060
Well, it's a misconception:

40:06.070 --> 40:09.300
We don't bury our secrets when we die.

40:09.320 --> 40:12.090
They bury us when we're alive.

40:16.620 --> 40:18.570
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

40:26.660 --> 40:28.540
Thanks.

40:30.460 --> 40:32.680
Uh, listen, Cynthia.

40:33.810 --> 40:35.240
I wanted to apologize.

40:35.290 --> 40:37.520
- For what?
- For being skeptical.

40:37.550 --> 40:39.359
You know, Cri/Res has
always been a family,

40:39.360 --> 40:43.299
just like you said in
your toast, and when

40:43.300 --> 40:45.780
you didn't seem interested in
being part of that family,

40:45.850 --> 40:47.280
I kind of got my back up.

40:47.300 --> 40:49.130
I want us to be straight
with each other.

40:49.170 --> 40:50.300
Cri/Res is all that matters,

40:50.340 --> 40:52.960
and you're a big part of that.

40:54.000 --> 40:55.600
Thanks, Oliver.

40:57.260 --> 41:00.059
And I got you this from Sandro.

41:00.060 --> 41:01.270
[LAUGHS]: You didn't.

41:01.310 --> 41:02.360
No way.

41:02.380 --> 41:04.270
You know, call it an olive branch.

41:04.320 --> 41:05.620
What do you say?

41:06.920 --> 41:08.380
I say,

41:08.400 --> 41:12.020
in light of what we now
know about the Ravenzos,

41:12.060 --> 41:14.020
- I'd settle for a handshake.
- Mm.

41:14.060 --> 41:15.500
I don't blame you.

41:15.540 --> 41:16.979
- All right.
- Thank you.

41:16.980 --> 41:19.320
Yeah.

41:38.310 --> 41:40.060
[SIGHS]

41:54.710 --> 41:56.500
[LIGHTER CLICKING]

42:04.280 --> 42:08.200
Happy birthday, sis.

42:09.100 --> 42:12.380
I thought I'd never see you again.

42:16.950 --> 42:19.130
Look at you.

42:21.600 --> 42:23.800
Who else knows you're here?

